      <description>&lt;p&gt;I have an idea for a paper I would like to write about 
&lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gandalf&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Gandolf&lt;/a&gt;&lt;!--Why does the aged one who is a sage go to an archive? what does this say about using the sage as a corporate identity profiles? or about archive managment--&gt;, but I would like to situate my arguments within the context of other literature about Gandolf. A trip to the library was in order to discover what sort of resources are out there to be consulted. A few years ago I ran across the Journal of Inklings Studies which was focused on all authors who were part of the writers circle, Inklings, which included J.R.R. Tolkien and C.S. Lewis. The series of journals to consult appear below. In addition there are newsletters from various societies which are not listed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.jstor.org/journal/tolkienj&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Tolkien Journal&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.jstor.org/journal/mythlore&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Mythlore&lt;/a&gt; ; 
&lt;a href=&#34;http://www.mythsoc.org/tolkien-journal.htm&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Community home page&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;a href=&#34;https://muse.jhu.edu/journal/299&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Tolkien Studies: An Annual Scholarly Review&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.tolkiensociety.org/society/publications/mallorn&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Mallorn&lt;/a&gt; — journal of the Tolkien Society&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.euppublishing.com/loi/ink&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Journal of Inklings Studies&lt;/a&gt; ; 
&lt;a href=&#34;http://inklings-studies.org&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;masthead&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
